
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.x-blue.svg)
![Tkinter](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tkinter-GUI-orange.svg)

A simple chatbot application built with Python and Tkinter. This chatbot provides information about storage unit sizes, location, operating hours, and more.

## Features

- Predefined responses for common user queries.
- User-friendly graphical user interface (GUI) built with Tkinter.
- Scrollable chat history.
- Easy-to-extend responses for the chatbot.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.x installed on your system.
- Tkinter library included with your Python installation.

### Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine using:

   ```shell
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/storage-unit-chatbot.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```shell
   cd storage-unit-chatbot
   ```

3. Run the application:

   ```shell
   python main.py
   ```

## Usage

- Type your message in the input field and press the "Send" button to interact with the chatbot.
- The chatbot will respond to predefined queries about storage unit information.

## Customization

You can customize the chatbot by modifying the `chatbot_responses` dictionary in the `main.py` file. Add your own responses to handle additional user queries.

```python
# Define predefined responses for the chatbot
chatbot_responses = {
    "hello": "Hello! How can I assist you today?",
    # Add more responses here
}
```

